summary: This is an FBI interview report (FD-302) documenting the interview of Julio Cesar Suarez on November 4, 2009, in Boca Raton, Florida. Suarez was interviewed regarding his presence at the Hilton Hotel with his friend Alfredo Rodriguez, who was there to deliver documents. The report details Suarez's background, his account of the day's events, and the release of Rodriguez's vehicle to him.

persons.name: Julio Cesar Suarez
persons.context: Interviewed by FBI agents regarding his travel to the Hilton Hotel in Boca Raton with Alfredo Rodriguez. He is a kitchen cabinet salesperson and a U.S. Permanent Resident.

persons.name: Alfredo Rodriguez
persons.context: Friend of Suarez who drove him to the Hilton Hotel to deliver unspecified documents. He rents the El Cristo restaurant in Miami.

connections.description: Friends who met through their wives. Rodriguez picked up Suarez to have lunch and drove him to the Hilton Hotel.

events.title: FBI Interview of Julio Cesar Suarez
events.description: FBI agents interviewed Julio Cesar Suarez near the Hilton Hotel in Boca Raton, Florida. He was advised of his rights and provided information about traveling with Alfredo Rodriguez, who was delivering documents.

locations: Hilton Hotel, 7920 Glades Road, Boca Raton, Florida
El Cristo restaurant, 8th Street, Miami, Florida
keyFacts: Alfredo Rodriguez was at the Hilton Hotel in Boca Raton to deliver unspecified documents, the nature of which Suarez claimed no knowledge.
Rodriguez rents the El Cristo restaurant in Miami and had FBI agents release his Chevrolet Trailblazer to Suarez after the interview.
Suarez is a U.S. Permanent Resident and kitchen cabinet salesperson who was interviewed under a formal FBI rights advisement (FD-395).
